# Modules used in this project
Tool Modules Used in This Project

Your project includes four main tool modules, each implemented as a separate Python class/module inside the modules/ directory.
 1. calculator.py

Purpose: Perform arithmetic operations.
Responsibilities:

Add, subtract, multiply, divide

Validate inputs

Handle division-by-zero errors

Provide clean method-based API (OOP)

Class Example:

class Calculator:
    def add(self, a, b):
        return a + b

 2. notes.py

Purpose: Manage user notes with file storage.
Responsibilities:

Create notes

View notes

List all notes

Edit notes

Delete notes

Search notes

Store notes in the data/notes folder

Handle file I/O safely

Class Example:

class NotesManager:
    def create(self, title, content):
        ...

 3. timer.py

Purpose: Provide countdown timer & stopwatch functionality.
Responsibilities:

Start / pause / stop stopwatch

Calculate elapsed time

Support countdown timers

Allow formatted time output

Use Python time module internally

Class Example:

class Timer:
    def start(self):
        ...

 4. file_organizer.py

Purpose: Automatically organize files in a directory.
Responsibilities:

Scan a folder

Sort files into categories (Images, Documents, Videos, etc.)

Create destination folders if not present

Move files safely

Backup option (optional)

Use file extensions from predefined mappings

Class Example:

class FileOrganizer:
    def organize(self, path):
        ...

 modules/ Folder Structure
modules/
│── __init__.py
│── calculator.py
│── notes.py
│── timer.py
└── file_organizer.py

 Additional Optional Modules (If You Want to Expand)

These are optional but useful:

 logger.py

Custom logging system.

 config_manager.py

Handles reading/writing config.json.

 backup_manager.py

Handles backups for notes or organized files.

 menu.py

Centralized class for displaying CLI menus.
